001package com.pingidentity.sdk.pingonewallet.types.WalletEvents;
002
003import com.pingidentity.did.sdk.client.service.model.Challenge;
004import com.pingidentity.sdk.pingonewallet.errors.PairingException;
005import com.pingidentity.sdk.pingonewallet.types.WalletMessage.pairing.PairingMessage;
006
007public class WalletPairingEvent implements WalletEvent {
008
009    public static WalletEventType TYPE = WalletEventType.PAIRING;
010
011    public String applicationInstanceId;
012    public String sender;
013    public Challenge challenge;
014
015    private PairingMessage pairingMessage;
016
017    public WalletPairingEvent(String applicationInstanceId, String sender, Challenge challenge, PairingMessage pairingMessage) {
018        this.applicationInstanceId = applicationInstanceId;
019        this.sender = sender;
020        this.challenge = challenge;
021        this.pairingMessage = pairingMessage;
022    }
023
024    @Override
025    public WalletEventType getType() {
026        return TYPE;
027    }
028
029    @Override
030    public String getSender() {
031        return sender;
032    }
033
034    @Override
035    public Challenge getChallenge() {
036        return challenge;
037    }
038
039    public boolean isSuccess(){
040        return pairingMessage.isSuccess();
041    }
042
043    public PairingException getError(){
044        return pairingMessage.getError();
045    }
046
047    public String getMessage() {
048        return pairingMessage.getRawMessage();
049    }
050
051    public String getApplicationInstanceId() {
052        return applicationInstanceId;
053    }
054}
